main event: Unidentified aerial objects were reported observed at Sheppard Air Force Base.
interesting points: The observation occurred on May 4, 1951, and lasted for approximately 30 seconds., Between ten to fifteen objects were seen moving from east to northwest., The sightings were evaluated and suggested to be a flock of birds or possibly a balloon or aircraft., The objects were observed at a high altitude, estimated between 35,000 to 40,000 feet., The report includes statements by USAF personnel involved in the observation.
